<subSubSection id="C3486535CD7FFFC96DFCFD70FE42FA34" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BED36BECD7FFFC96DFCFD70FDD5FC51" blockId="8.[151,1437,672,1633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B926EAACCD7FFFC96DFCFD70FE80FD78" bold="true" box="[199,345,672,697]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">Description.</emphasis>
See 
<tableCitation id="C6D00305CD7FFFC96CA3FD70FE22FD78" box="[408,507,672,697]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1343,308,1270]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphometric data of for BarIlIus ardens (n = 6, ZSI / SRC, F. 8812, F. 8813, MKC 385), B. canarensIs (n = 3, ZSI / SRC, F. 8814, MKC 415), B. malabarIcus (n = 10, ZSI / SRC, F. 8815, F. 8816, MKC 416), B. bakerI (n = 6, MKC 295, 384)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF2D6636CD75FFC36DACFF48FF16FF2E" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" tableUuid="DF2D6636CD75FFC36DACFF48FF16FF2E">
Tables 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96CD6FD71FE22FD78" box="[493,507,673,697]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
and 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96F07FD71FD93FD78" box="[572,586,673,697]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">
<tableCitation id="C6D00305CD7FFFC96F07FD71FD93FD78" box="[572,586,673,697]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,239,1338,1361]" captionTargetBox="[159,1314,1421,1856]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 2. Meristic data of BarIlIus ardens (n = 6, ZSI / SRC, F. 8812, F. 8813, MKC 385), B. canarensIs (n = 3, ZSI / SRC, F. 8814, MKC 415), B. malabarIcus (n = 10, ZSI / SRC, F. 8815, F. 8816, MKC 416), B. bakerI (n = 6, MKC 295, 384)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF2D6636CD75FFC36DACFAEAFA83FAB0" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" tableUuid="DF2D6636CD75FFC36DACFAEAFA83FAB0">2</tableCitation>
</number>
for morphometric and meristic characters, and 
<figureCitation id="13692A3BCD7FFFC969BAFD70FB28FD78" box="[1153,1265,672,697]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,553,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[217,1369,553,1823]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Barilius malabaricus, A, unregistered specimen in life from aquarium trade ~ 80 mm SL, Kannur, Kerala; B, MKC 416, prior to fixation, 61.8 mm SL, Valapattanam river, Kerala; C, ZSI / SRC, F. 8816, prior to fixation, 76.8 mm SL, Payaswini River, Kerala." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242898/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">Figures 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13692A3BCD7FFFC96839FD71FAC9FD79" box="[1282,1296,673,696]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,611,633]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,589]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[217,1369,193,590]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Barilius malabaricus, ZSI / SRC, F. 8815, 90.7 mm SL, Payaswini River, Kerala." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242899/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">7</figureCitation>
for general appearance. Body deep, depth about one-third SL, laterally compressed, dorsal profile slightly curved, ventral profile deeply convex. Caudal peduncle deep, depth almost equal to length. Head small, length about one-fourth SL, depth more than three-fourths length, dorsal profile almost straight, a slightly raised at nape. Eyes large, placed forward, diameter about one-third HL. Mouth oblique, angle of gape reaching middle of orbit. Two pairs of minute barbels (rostral and maxillary). Nostrils closer to eye than to snout tip. Lower jaw slightly longer than upper jaw. Snout length about one-third HL.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED36BECD7FFFC96DFCFC4CFDCBFB14" blockId="8.[151,1437,672,1633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
Dorsal fin with 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96C4EFC4DFE5AFC74" box="[373,387,925,949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
simple and 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96F31FC4CFDFDFC74" box="[522,548,924,949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="11.0">11</number>
½ (
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96F72FC4DFDBFFC74" box="[585,614,925,949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="10.0">10</number>
) branched rays, posterior margin slightly concave, origin anterior to analfin origin. Pelvic fin short, not reaching anal-fin origin, with 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96E6FFC11FCBBFC18" box="[852,866,961,985]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
simple and 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96ED4FC11FC24FC18" box="[1007,1021,961,985]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96934FC11FBF5FC18" box="[1039,1068,961,985]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="10.0">10</number>
) branched rays. Anal fin with 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC968B5FC11FA45FC18" box="[1422,1436,961,985]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
simple and 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96C1FFC34FEE6FC3C" box="[292,319,996,1021]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="14.0">14</number>
½ (
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96C51FC34FEA1FC3C" box="[362,376,996,1021]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="7.0">7</number>
)– 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96CAAFC34FE75FC3C" box="[401,428,996,1021]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="15.0">15</number>
½ (
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96CE3FC35FE3FFC3C" box="[472,486,997,1021]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
) branched rays, ventral margin deeply concave, a sharp curve among first few branched rays. Pectoral fin with 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96F25FBD9FDF5FBE0" box="[542,556,1033,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
simple and 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96FFEFBD9FD39FBE0" box="[709,736,1033,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="11.0">11</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96FCEFBD9FCDAFBE0" box="[757,771,1033,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="7.0">7</number>
)– 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96E20FBD9FCEEFBE0" box="[795,823,1033,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="12.0">12</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96E76FBD9FC82FBE0" box="[845,859,1033,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
) branched rays. Caudal fin deeply forked, lobes subequal, lower lobe slightly longer, with 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96F49FBFDFDA5FB84" box="[626,636,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96FB5FBFDFD44FB84" box="[654,669,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="9.0">9</number>
+ 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96F8BFBFDFD67FB84" box="[688,702,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="8.0">8</number>
+ 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96FEBFBFDFD03FB84" box="[720,730,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
rays. Lateral line complete, slightly curved with 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC9683EFBFCFAF8FB84" box="[1285,1313,1068,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="36.0">36</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96809FBFDFA9BFB84" box="[1330,1346,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="7.0">7</number>
), 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96863FBFDFAADFB84" box="[1368,1396,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="37.0">37</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC968BFFBFDFA4AFB84" box="[1412,1427,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
) or 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96D8EFB81FF08FBA8" box="[181,209,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="38.0">38</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96DD8FB81FF36FBA8" box="[227,239,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
) + 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96C23FB81FEFFFBA8" box="[280,294,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96C0DFB81FE8AFBA8" box="[310,339,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="10.0">10</number>
) pored scales. Predorsal scales 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96F8CFB80FD0DFBA8" box="[695,724,1104,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="15.0">15</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96FE5FB80FD34FBA8" box="[734,749,1104,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="6.0">6</number>
), 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96E38FB80FCC6FBA8" box="[771,799,1104,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="16.0">16</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96E15FB81FCE4FBA8" box="[814,829,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
) or 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96E56FB81FC50FBA8" box="[877,905,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="17.0">17</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96EA2FB81FC70FBA8" box="[921,937,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
); scales in transverse line on body ½ 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96871FB80FA8EFBA8" box="[1354,1367,1104,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="9.0">9</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96853FB81FAA1FBA8" box="[1384,1400,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="4.0">4</number>
), 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC968B5FB81FA45FBA8" box="[1422,1436,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="9.0">9</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96D9BFBA5FF76FB4C" box="[160,175,1141,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
), ½ 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96DE6FBA4FF33FB4C" box="[221,234,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96DC0FBA5FED0FB4C" box="[251,265,1141,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
) / 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96C1FFBA4FEF4FB4C" box="[292,301,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96C0DFBA4FE9DFB4C" box="[310,324,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
½ (
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96C50FBA4FEA0FB4C" box="[363,377,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="5.0">5</number>
)– 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96CA9FBA4FE46FB4C" box="[402,415,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96C8BFBA4FE67FB4C" box="[432,446,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="5.0">5</number>
) between dorsal-fin origin and pelvic-fin base, 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96EE0FBA4FC30FB4C" box="[987,1001,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
½ (
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96934FBA4FBC4FB4C" box="[1039,1053,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="5.0">5</number>
)– 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC9690DFBA4FB9AFB4C" box="[1078,1091,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC9696FFBA4FBBBFB4C" box="[1108,1122,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="5.0">5</number>
) scales between lateral line and anal-fin base. Gill rakers slender, well-defined, 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96FC6FB49FCD2FB70" box="[765,779,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96E1AFB49FCE9FB70" box="[801,816,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
), 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96E70FB49FC80FB70" box="[843,857,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96E55FB49FCA4FB70" box="[878,893,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="7.0">7</number>
) + 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96E96FB49FC62FB70" box="[941,955,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96EEBFB49FC06FB70" box="[976,991,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
), 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96EC1FB49FBD1FB70" box="[1018,1032,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="9.0">9</number>
(
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96926FB49FBF5FB70" box="[1053,1068,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="7.0">7</number>
) rakers on first gill arch. Fifth ceratobranchial with 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96CB8FB6CFE49FB14" box="[387,400,1212,1237]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="5.0">5</number>
+ 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96C9BFB6CFE76FB14" box="[416,431,1212,1237]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96C84FB6CFE14FB14" box="[447,461,1212,1237]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED36BECD7FFFC96DFCFB30FB85FA48" blockId="8.[151,1437,672,1633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B926EAACCD7FFFC96DFCFB30FE96FB38" bold="true" box="[199,335,1248,1273]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">Coloration.</emphasis>
In life (see 
<figureCitation id="13692A3BCD7FFFC96CEFFB30FDCEFB38" box="[468,535,1248,1273]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,553,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[217,1369,553,1823]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Barilius malabaricus, A, unregistered specimen in life from aquarium trade ~ 80 mm SL, Kannur, Kerala; B, MKC 416, prior to fixation, 61.8 mm SL, Valapattanam river, Kerala; C, ZSI / SRC, F. 8816, prior to fixation, 76.8 mm SL, Payaswini River, Kerala." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242898/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96F3CFB30FDCEFB38" box="[519,535,1248,1273]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
), body bright bluish-silver with one or two rows of spots on flank, first row with 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96DACFAD5FF04FADC" box="[151,221,1285,1309]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13</number>
round or oval bluish-green spots 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96F53FAD5FD48FADC" box="[616,657,1285,1309]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
scales high and 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96E6CFAD5FC58FADC" box="[855,897,1285,1309]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
scales wide, second row (if present) with 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96849FAD5FA45FADC" box="[1394,1436,1285,1309]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
smaller spots reaching up to anal-fin origin. Sometimes in large specimens spots of second row further break up into a smaller third row consisting of 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96F04FA9DFDB0FAA4" box="[575,617,1357,1381]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
minute spots. Dorsal fin and anal fin bases black, fin margins lined with orange sometime mixed with white. Caudal fin black, medial rays and lobe tips white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED36BECD7FFFC96DFCFA44FE42FA34" blockId="8.[151,1437,672,1633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
Preserved specimens (
<figureCitation id="13692A3BCD7FFFC96CFFFA44FDD3FA6C" box="[452,522,1428,1453]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,611,633]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,589]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[217,1369,193,590]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Barilius malabaricus, ZSI / SRC, F. 8815, 90.7 mm SL, Payaswini River, Kerala." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242899/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9A2499CD7FFFC96CC0FA45FDD3FA6C" box="[507,522,1429,1453]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) lose bright colours: greyish, darker on the dorsal side, progressively becoming lighters towards the abdomen, which is white. The spots on body dark grey. Fins opaque, dorsal, anal and caudal with black bases black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3486535CD7FFFC96DFCF9D0FE9AF9A0" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BED36BECD7FFFC96DFCF9D0FE9AF9A0" blockId="8.[151,1437,672,1633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B926EAACCD7FFFC96DFCF9D0FEB9F9D8" bold="true" box="[199,352,1536,1561]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C524D3DCD7FFFC96C5DF9D1FD8AF9D8" box="[358,595,1537,1561]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malabaricus">
<emphasis id="B926EAACCD7FFFC96C5DF9D1FD8AF9D8" box="[358,595,1537,1561]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">Barilius malabaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from the Payaswini and Vallapattanam Rivers, both of which flow through north Kerala, but probably occurs throughout a wider range in the southern Karnataka and northern Kerala regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
